{{Infobox organization | name = Berkeley Initiative for Transparency in the Social Sciences | native_name = <!-- Organization's name in its local language --> | native_name_lang = <!-- ISO code of the above language --> | named_after = | image = | image_size = | alt = <!-- see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- map image --> | map_size = <!-- defaults to 250px --> | map_alt = | map_caption = | map2 = <!-- second map image, if required --> | map2_size = | map2_alt = | map2_caption = | abbreviation = BITSS | motto = | predecessor = | merged = <!-- Any other organizations with which the organization was merged --> | successor = | formation = 2012 | founder = [[Edward Miguel]] | founding_location = | extinction = <!-- or: | dissolved = --> <!--e.g. use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | merger = <!-- Other organizations (if any) merged to constitute the organization --> | type = Initiative | status = <!-- Organization's legal status and/or description (company, charity, foundation, etc) --> | purpose = Promoting [[open research]] in the [[social sciences]] | professional_title = <!-- for professional associations --> | headquarters = [[Berkeley, California|Berkeley]], [[California]] | location = | coords = <!-- location's {{coord}}s --> | region = <!-- or: | region_served = --> <!--Any particular region or regions associated with or served by the organization--> | services = | membership = <!-- Usually the number of members --> | membership_year = <!-- Year to which membership number/data apply --> | language = <!-- or: | languages = --> <!--Any official language or languages used by the organization--> | sec_gen = <!-- Name of the organization's Secretary General (if post exists) --> | leader_title = Faculty Director | leader_name = [[Edward Miguel]] | leader_title2 = Program Advisor | leader_name2 = Jennifer Sturdy | leader_title3 = Interim Program Manager | leader_name3 = Katie Hoeberling | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = <!-- or: | publication = --> <!--Organization's principal body (assembly, committee, board, etc) or publication--> | parent_organization = [[Center for Effective Global Action]] | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | staff = <!-- Numbers and/or types of staff --> | staff_year = <!-- Year to which staff numbers/data apply --> | volunteers = <!-- Numbers and/or types of volunteers --> | volunteers_year = <!-- Year to which volunteer numbers/data apply --> | website = {{url|https://www.bitss.org/}} | remarks = | formerly = <!-- Any former names by which the organization known --> | footnotes = }} The '''Berkeley Initiative for Transparency in the Social Sciences''', abbreviated '''BITSS''', is an academic initiative dedicated to advancing [[transparency]] and openness in [[social science]] research. It was established in 2012 by the [[University of California, Berkeley]]'s [[Center for Effective Global Action]]. It is led by an interdisciplinary group of academics from ten different universities.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bitss.org/about/ |title=About |date=2015-10-08 |website=Berkeley Initiative for Transparency in the Social Sciences |language=en-US |access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> It has worked with the [[Center for Open Science]] to define and promote a set of best practices for social scientists to maximize transparency in their research.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Miguel |first=E. |last2=Camerer |first2=C. |last3=Casey |first3=K. |last4=Cohen |first4=J. |last5=Esterling |first5=K. M. |last6=Gerber |first6=A. |last7=Glennerster |first7=R. |last8=Green |first8=D. P. |last9=Humphreys |first9=M. |date=2014-01-03 |title=Promoting Transparency in Social Science Research |url=http://science.sciencemag.org/content/343/6166/30 |journal=Science |language=en |volume=343 |issue=6166 |pages=30–31 |doi=10.1126/science.1245317 |issn=0036-8075 |pmc=4103621 |pmid=24385620}}</ref>
In 2015, the BITSS began awarding the annual Leamer-Rosenthal Prizes for Open Social Science to honor outstanding achievements in promoting transparency in social science.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2015/12/make-science-more-reliable-win-cash-prizes/419781/ |title=Make Science More Reliable, Win Cash Prizes |last=Yong |first=Ed |date=2015-12-10 |website=The Atlantic |language=en-US |access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> Through its Catalyst program, the initiative also supports over 120 [[graduate student]]s who are active in advancing [[open science]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bitss.org/catalysts/ |title=Catalysts |date=2015-12-03 |website=Berkeley Initiative for Transparency in the Social Sciences |language=en-US |access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> ==References== {{Reflist}} ==External links== *{{Official website|https://www.bitss.org/}} {{Science-org-stub}}
