'''Bioregenerative [[life support system]]s''' ('''BLSS''') are artificial ecosystems consisting of many complex symbiotic relationships among [[higher plants]], [[animal]]s, and [[microorganisms]]. As the most advanced [[Life support system|life support]] technology, BLSS can provide a habitation environment similar to the Earth's [[biosphere]] for [[space missions]] with extended durations, in [[outer space|deep space]], and with multiple crews.<ref>{{cite book|last=Liu|first=Hong|title=Bioregenerative Life Support Systems in Space: A Research Update. New Developments in Science and Technology - 60th Anniversary Special Issue, Beihang University (BUAA)|year=2012|publisher=A Sponsored Supplement To Science|pages=86–87|display-authors=etal}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Mitchell|first=CA|title=Bioregenerative life-support systems|journal=Am J Clin Nutr|year=1994|volume=60|issue=5|pages=820S-824S}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Sheehy|first=Cody|title="Earthlight" Documentary|url=http://cals.arizona.edu/earthlight}}</ref>
